      "message": "The Logical operator \u0027and\u0027 has higher precedence than \u0027or\u0027.\n\nThis sentence leads into a bug when the log_management_button is enable but user doesn\u0027t has permission to access Kibana.\n\nThis issue can not be solved by adding parenthesis, because it is a Django template [1]\n\nAlthough is possible to fix it in one logical sentence:\n\n(a or b) and c\nnot ( not ((a or b) and c) )\nnot ( not (a or b) or not c )\nnot ( not a and not b or not c )\n\nIn this case:\n\n{% if not enable_log_management_button and not enable_event_management_button or not can_access_kibana %}\n{% else %}\n\u003cPrint the button\u003e\n{% endif %}\n\n... or just use nested ifs.\n\n[1] https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/templates/builtins/?from\u003dolddocs#complex-expressions",
